Department of Chemistry

   The Department of Chemistry was established in the year 1964 as an Undergraduate programme. It was upgraded into a Postgraduate department in 1984 and was approved as a research centre by the Manonmanium Sundaranar University in 2007. The department of chemistry is well known for its excellence in teaching and research. All of our department staff members are approved research guides and are actively participated in research. The department has produced about 60 Ph.D., students and has a good number of publications in National/International level journals. Staff of our department has operated several minor and major projects and many of them have worked as Young Scientists at various research centers.

   In addition to the regular curriculum the department offers career oriented certificate courses for both UG and PG students. The department has 3 spacious labs with the latest technological gizmos to strengthen their base of the students in their subject. The Department has provided support by way of access to its Department library, digital smart board, research journals, analytical facilities, instrumentation support and guidance.
